I’d give 6 stars if I I could. This is only my 2nd time having Ledo’s Pizza. We were craving pizza and the recent reviews of the other local pizza restaurants were kinda bad. Saw good reviews for the Ledo’s on GA Avenue so figured I’d try it out. Long story short, I ordered online in advance. Got to the restaurant a few minutes early and was pleasantly surprised at the curbside service (after a year of quarantine and lots of curbside restaurant experiences, this is one of the few that’s actually doing a great job at true curbside, socially-distanced service). By the time I gave the young man my name and looked for a spot to wait in the lot, another server was already bringing the food to the car. Wanted to wait until after we ate to post this review. The food was delicious (deluxe pizza, wings, salad, and calzone). I’ll DEFINITELY be ordering from this location again.
